articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: European Union businesses are concerned about China's data laws, including their "lack of clarity" and the "long processes" that companies have to undergo, European Commission Vice President Vera Jourova said on Tuesday.
articles.title: EU says lack of clarity in China's data laws is concerning

articles.author: David Dolan
articles.description: At factories in Japan's industrial heartland, Toyota (7203.T) has turned to self-propelled assembly lines, massive die casting and even old-fashioned hand polishing as it aims to make up for lost ground in battery electric vehicles.
articles.title: In EV battle, Toyota bets on new technology and old-school thinking

articles.author: Casey Hall
articles.description: Geopolitics and a slowing economy are fuelling pessimism among U.S. businesses operating in China, with the proportion of firms optimistic about their five-year outlook in the country falling to a record low, a survey released on Tuesday said.
articles.title: U.S. business optimism about China outlook falls to record low - survey

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Chinese developers Sunac (1918.HK) and Country Garden (2007.HK) brought some relief to the crisis-hit property sector by forging debt deals with creditors, but the outlook remained clouded by uncertainty about a recovery in home sales.
articles.title: Sunac, Country Garden debt deals bring respite for China's property sector

articles.author: David Shepardson, Joseph White
articles.description: Ford Motor (F.N) could face a strike in Canada if no agreement is reached by 11:59 p.m. Monday with the union representing about 5,600 Canadian auto workers, just days after workers at one of its U.S. plants went on strike.
articles.title: Ford could face strike in Canada, adding to US labor pressure

articles.author: Yantoultra Ngui, Scott Murdoch
articles.description: Several Southeast Asian companies are considering listing in the United States, banking on strong investor appetite for emerging market growth in the absence of Chinese stock offerings.
articles.title: More SE Asia firms consider U.S. IPOs, filling void left by China peers

articles.author: Howard Schneider
articles.description: U.S. Federal Reserve officials, who have tentatively embraced the possibility they can squelch inflation without a recession, meet this week with an autoworkers strike, a possible federal government shutdown, and a student loan squeeze on consumers posing new risks to that best-case outcome.
articles.title: The Fed wants to cool spending; a strike, a shutdown and student loans may add ice

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: India characterised as "absurd and motivated" an accusation by Canada that it was involved in the murder of a Sikh separatist leader, urging the country instead to take legal action against anti-Indian elements operating from its soil.
articles.title: India dismisses as 'absurd' Canada's accusation on Sikh leader's murder

articles.author: Andrew Mills
articles.description: A Qatari plane waited in Iran on Monday to fly out five U.S. detainees in a swap for five Iranians held in the United States, thanks to a Doha-mediated deal that has also unfrozen $6 billion of Iranian funds.
articles.title: US and Iran to swap detainees after $6 billion unfrozen

articles.author: Sheila Dang, Ari Rabinovitch
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu urged Elon Musk to strike a balance between protecting free expression and fighting hate speech at a meeting on Monday after weeks of controversy over antisemitic content on Musk's social media platform X.
articles.title: Israel's Netanyahu urges Musk to balance free speech, fighting hate on X
